Detailed Description

This is the base class from which all other property readers will derive.
This class is responsible for reading the file and creating an IReader.
The derived class has to implement openChild, processChildData and closeChild which will process the xml files

virtual void OpenViBEApplications::ExternalP300PropertyReader::readPropertiesFromFile ( OpenViBE::CString  propertyFile) [virtual]

This methods opens and reads the file into a buffer. This buffer pointer is then used to create a XML reader object. The process function is called on this object which will consequently call the functions openChild, processChildData and closeChild implemented in the derived classes

Parameters:
propertyFilethe xml file from which we wish to read the properties
